But how does React know which card is which? It doesn't. All six cards would look exactly the same. So we need a way to send different data to each card. That's where Props come in.



1. What are Props?
Answer: Props stands for Properties. Think of Props as information that one component sends to another component.
Imagine your mother asks you: "Bring me a cup of tea."She gives you information: Tea, One cup, Less sugar. That information is like Props.


2. Real-Life Example
Imagine you're a teacher. You have one report card template. Instead of creating a new report card for every student, you fill in different details.
Student 1:
 Name: Rahul
 Marks: 95

Student 2:
 Name: Priya
