The template is the Component.The student details are the Props.



3. React Example

Imagine this component: <Card />
Now we pass information. <Card title="Passport" />
Another one: <Card title="Driving License" />
Another: <Card title="Birth Certificate" />
Same component. Different data.That's the power of Props.



4. Parent and Child

This is a term you'll hear everywhere, imagine: 
App
│
├── Navbar
├── Hero
├── Card
└── Footer       

App uses Card, So:  
App = Parent
Card = Child,   The Parent sends Props to the Child. Think of it like: Parent
           │
           │ Sends Data
           ▼
         Child
Remember this forever: Props always flow from Parent to Child.


5. Why do we use Props?
Answer:  Without Props: You create six different card components.
PassportCard, DrivingLicenseCard, BirthCertificateCard, PanCard, AadhaarCard
Lots of repeated code. With Props: You create only one. <Card /> And change only the information you pass. That's why React applications stay clean and reusable.






