Interview Question

Q1. What are Props in React?
A good answer: Props (Properties) are used to pass data from a parent component to a child component. They make components reusable by allowing the same component to display different information.

Q2. Why do we use Props?
A strong answer would be: "Props allow us to pass data from a parent component to a child component. They help us reuse the same component with different data, reducing duplicate code and making applications easier to maintain."


📝 Homework (15–20 minutes)
Part 1 (Theory)

Q1 What are Props?
Answer: Props stands for properties. They make components reusable by allowing one component or same component to display different information.  

One small improvement: Props don't make a component reusable by themselves—they allow us to pass different data to the same reusable component.

A slightly better answer would be: Props (Properties) are used to pass data from a parent component to a child component. They allow the same component to display different information, making it reusable.




Q2 Why do we use Props?
Answer: We use Props to make code clean and  easy to understand by avoiding same code multiple time, we use only one component to display different information, the data flow from parent component to child component.
Excellent! You included:
✅ Reusability
✅ Clean code
✅ Parent → Child
Those are the three main reasons.



Q3 Who sends Props? Parent, child, Both Explain your answer.
Answer: The parents sends Propes to child component because parents components uses the child component to show different information. Remember this forever:
Parent
   │
   │ Props
   ▼
Child

Props always travel downward. Later, we'll learn how a child component can communicate back to a parent using callback functions, but Props themselves are one-way.




Q4 Can one Card component display different service names? If yes, how?
Answer: Yes one Card component can display different service name using props , props make it possible to display different info. using same card (component).



